laboratory_examinations.findings: The hepatic parenchyma appears within normal limits. The contour of the liver is smooth. There is no focal liver mass. Small hepatic cysts, the largest measuring up to 0.5 cm noted. No intrahepatic biliary dilation. The CHD measures 6 mm. The gallbladder appears distended with a large stone seen in the gallbladder neck. No definite pericholecystic fluid or gallbladder wall thickening noted. The pancreas appears within normal limits. Limited views of the right kidney show no hydronephrosis.
MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
